# Implementation Plan - Refactoring UML Diagrams to English and Standard Coding Conventions

We will translate all Spanish class names, attributes, methods, and types in the Yupay Finance UML diagrams to English, utilizing professional fintech and banking terminology. We will also apply standard PascalCase for classes/enums and camelCase for attributes/methods, ensuring consistent data types (e.g., `String`, `int`, `double`, `boolean`, `Date`).

## Proposed Translations Mapping

### Core Enums & Entity Mappings
| Spanish | English (PascalCase / UPPERCASE) | Notes |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| `Usuario` | `User` | Standard |
| `EntidadFinanciera` | `FinancialInstitution` | Fintech standard |
| `TipoEntidad` | `InstitutionType` | Enums: `BANK` (for `BANCO`), `SAVINGS_BANK` (for `CAJA`), `COOPERATIVE` (for `COOPERATIVA`) |
| `TipoMoneda` | `CurrencyType` | Enums: `PEN` (for `SOLES`), `USD` (for `DOLARES`) |
| `TipoSuscripcion` | `SubscriptionType` | Enums: `BASIC` (for `BASICO`), `PRO` (for `PRO`) |

